value.title: Tumblr Likes copy
value.description:
Get a feed of your Tumblr Likes. Unlike other pipes which do this, this one queries the Tumblr API, hence the need for your Tumblr credentials. Tumblr API limits the maximum number of Likes to fetch to 50. 

NOTES: this defaults to my Likes. To display yours, you have two options: 1 / enter your Tumblr credentials  (the email address your registered with Tumblr and your Tumblr password) below or 2 / clone the pipe and store the credentials as default values in the two first Private Input fields (do not forget to check “private”). Option 1, the form below, is only recommended for testing, as your Tumblr password will be embedded in plaintext in the pipe URL (this is a limitation of Tumblr’s authentication scheme in conjunction with the Pipes system and is not under my control). For a more secure use, resort to option 2, cloning.

items.regular-body:
I’m calling it.  As of yesterday at 4PM, I have been smoke free for a full week.  On top of that, I have not been using nicotine in any form (patch, inhaler, gum) for over 4 days.  I’ve quit smoking successfully.

I know it might be a little premature to call it, but I know me.  The worst part is over, and I’m not suffering through the days anymore.  I still have cravings, but I can handle that and keep moving forward.

Thank you everyone for your support along the way, it helped tremendously.  A special thanks to my wife for not only being a huge supporter, but dealing with a cranky, nicotine-fiending husband.  Thanks Allison, I love you.
